```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "deepstem101",
    "output_log_file": "sbatch_log/pytorch-1gpu.%j.out",
    "gpu_queue": "3090",
    "max_runtime": "3-00:00:00",
    "gpu_count": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "python_script": "train_AL.py",
    "python_script_arguments": "-p checkpoint/deepstem101_bvsb_bdrytrim5x5 --model deeplabv3pluswn_resnet101deepstem --init_checkpoint checkpoint/city_res101deepstem_imagenet_pretrained.tar --method active_joint_multi_predignore_lossdecomp --active_method my_bvsb_banignore --or_labeling --fair_counting --loss_type joint_multi_loss --nseg 2048 --scheduler poly --train_lr 0.00002 --start_over --num_workers 12 --finetune_itrs 80000 --val_period 5000 --val_start 0 --separable_conv --max_iterations 5 --train_transform rescale_769_multi_notrg --loader region_cityscapes_or_tensor --active_selection_size 100000 --wandb_tags 50k base cos --init_iteration 1 --multi_ce_temp 0.1 --group_ce_temp 0.1 --ce_temp 0.1 --coeff 16.0 --coeff_mc 8.0 --coeff_gm 1.0 --init_iteration 1 --trim_kernel_size 5 --trim_multihot_boundary"
  }
}
```

The script is running on SLURM, a workload manager that allows for the scheduling of jobs across a cluster. It utilizes a single GPU from the "3090" queue and runs for a maximum of 3 hours. The script also requires 10 CPU cores per task and runs a Python script named "train_AL.py" with several arguments. 

The script also uses the `nvidia-smi` command to display information about the GPU, which suggests it is likely running a deep learning model. The script sets the `WANDB_SPAWN_METHOD` environment variable to "fork" which indicates the usage of Weights & Biases for tracking experiments.
